 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Junior Salesforce Developer (13782) Baer Group Washington, DC Remote **Federal Projects - Applicants Required to be United States Citizens with ability to obtain Public Trust Clearance** 
 The Baer Group is looking for Junior Salesforce Developer for 12+ Months Federal Remote Project. 
 Title:  Junior Salesforce Developer 
 Location:  Remote (Must be based in US) 
 Duration:  12 Months 
 Rate:  All-Inclusive 
 
 Description: 
 Develops the application including configuration, report development and data migration, where applicable 
 Performs custom development (as required) for 3rd party integrations using APIs 
 Carries out unit-testing and defect resolution 
 Carries out migration of the changes to production 
 Assists with technical design and documentation 
 Collaborates with internal stakeholders and team members to build solutions in SFDC that support business requirements 
 Assists with UAT and requirement validation 
 Development on Salesforce platform to meet project deliverables and goals 
 Builds Salesforce solutions using configuration/custom code and supports integrations 
 Supports build activities, using Visualforce, APEX, Force.com APIs, and Web Services. Sales/Service Cloud experience including design and development of Sales/Service Cloud 
 
 Requirements 
 1+ years of Salesforce Development experience 
 2 years of CSS experience 
 2 years of HTML experience 
 2 years of JavaScript experience 
 1+ years of Apex experience 
 
 Company Overview: 
 The Baer Group is an Enterprise Technology Consulting firm based in Atlanta, GA providing job opportunities with several 1st Tier Global Systems Integrators and a wide array of Fortune 1000 clients. Consultants and Employees of TBG enjoy access to the highest profile job opportunities across leading Enterprise Technology Solutions ranging from Digital Transformation programs utilizing the latest technologies from SAP and Oracle to a wide range of emerging Cloud based infrastructure, application and AI related solutions. 
